text: Bendix wasn¬¥t at Horsens, but he arranged a couch for us at his place. We had a good time with his flatmate Boris and his friends. Thank you for that generous help and hope we can meet in another moment in Denmark.
It was my first and i think that Already the best time :)

Bendix accepted me and my friend practically at the last minute when we could not find the accommodation. He was very involved in our arrival and was asking when we come. He offered us the opportunity to spend time with his friends, but he did not mind when we wanted to explore the city ourselves. His roommate is very nice and he cooks very well. Thanks to them, we could feel at home at home, and it is great to mention the time spent together. Really thanks guys!!

Bendix is quite busy at the weekday. But still host me and cook the nice fry rice. I m happy and enjoy my stay. Listening the music he played. Only too bad I can't stay till weekend for fun with them. :). But nice too stay with him and his funny housemate. :)

I stayed with Bendix and his roommate Boris in Horsens for the weekend. This was my first time ever Couchsurfing with someone that i truly did not know at all beforehand.  That being said, i didnt really know what to expect going into it, but i quickly realized that i had nothing to worry about when Bendix helped me make my travel arrangements to get to Horsens. Upon arriving, i was greeted by Bendix before i had even taken three steps off of the bus and that was a precursor to how things would go because Bendix maintained that level of courtesy for the entire weekend.  He has a good group of friends and i was introduced to all of them by Bendix himself. His roommate is also extremely friendly and would cook for me without me asking and would always offer tea/coffee whenever he was making some for himself. I genuinely felt like i was treated like family and was truly able to make myself at home.  Literally could not have imagined a better experience. They were also fun to party with ü§ô
Bendix is a great guy. Very friendly and flexible. I had a great stay and can recommend staying there.

Bendix is very nice and treat us as a friend. He has a very interesting conversation and his travel around the south asia was amazing. We are very thankful of his hospitality. Your roommate Boris is very friendly and interesting too.

Bendix was a blast to stay with. Not only was he a very welcoming and friendly host, he was also willing to show me around town and teach me a lot about the town itself. And as the icing on the cake, he is a great guy and was really fun to hang out with and talk to.

Leonard was a very nice and sociable person. He helped cook and clean when it was dinner time. I requested in advance that he be prepared to leave when I had to go to work and he complied with this. You will be glad to know him and you will not have concerns with him being in your home.

It was a pleasure to have Leonard around, we had a good talk, tried out some really good Denish food that he cooked, Leonard also gave me lots of advice on where my next trip should be which really helpful. Overall it was a really good experience.

Leonard was a very nice traveller. We had an amazing time at the medieval festival together and he seems to be always willing to have deep meaningful conversations. He also cooked delicious Romanian food for us.

Leo and Rose make a nice couple. I like the way they intake it all. They seem the kind of people who would never give up or step back, but keep pushing forward, which state I enjoyed having around. Leo is a good cook as well. And since Rose has an affinity for manaliga, there you have some happy people. Thanks guys for stopping by :)

Stayed with Leo and his girlfriend Rose for two nights. I had a really great time, cooking Romanian food, talking and playing games. We also went to the medieval festival together. Loved hanging out with them and their roommates!

Stayed with Rose and her boyfriend for a night while I  was bycicle Touring in Scandinavia. We had lots of fun playing boardgames and chatting after we cooked a nice dinner. Would definitely stay with her again anytime! Too bad that I won't pass through Horsens when I go home.

Rose hosted me for the Medieval Festival in Horsens and we went there together as we both share this interest. We had a great time taking pictures in our outfits, having Mj√∏d wine, medieval food and activities. As a person, Rose is very kind and thoughtful, trying to accommodate me as well as possible during the stay. We played board games at home and we had a lot of fun doing that, joked a lot around and has a great time. Would definitely host or be hosted by Rose any time, anywhere! :)

He's a friendly people who has a lot of conversation about sport and travel, and has interesting things to say. He was open for tasted new dishes and wine. He's very patient because i don't speak well english, and he helped me for understand what he was saying ! Thanks ! I recommend

was fun to host him, had some interesting chats about mountains, paragliding and climbing, went on walks around town and showed some stuffs . also a nice interesting surfer. will hsot him again soon too... recomended to host/surf with

text:
Vytenƒó and Jurgita were hitchhiking from Horsens  in Denmark to Nijmegen and decided spontaneously to stay in Groningen for a night. 
Vytenƒó is easy going, chill and cheerful. She likes to play boardgames and cardgames, she is a good guest, polite and friendly, I recommend hosting her.
Vytene stayed less 12h before she and her friend has to hit the road again but she was a cool guest, and gave me a candy for breakfast, miam :)

Having Vita and Jurgrita for two nights has brought joy, fun, and happiness to my place, they were both easy going and flexible. Vita is such a smart and kind girl who has taught me a new boarding game which I‚Äôm grateful for.

I hope life will give us the chance to meet again, take care!

Vytene was super fun to spend time with. She was energetic and entusiastic. She wanted to visit everything I suggested and we had fun doing so. She has a good humor and seems like a strong minded woman. Also, she brought some board games with her! We had fun playing Monopoly deal while waiting for food in the restaurant and in the evening with some tea. I found Vytene to be a warm, responsible and good humored guest. I would take her in as my guest again anytime. Cheers!

Vytene stayed at my place in Hamburg for one night and two days and was very eager to do all the things that I had in mind for the weekend! She is fun and up for everything and we went canueing in the canels of Hamburg, as well as visited a lot of other sights in Hamburg

Vyte and Vika were just fantastic guests. I totally enjoyed their presence, they are fun to be with and to talk to. The only problem I have with them is that they didn't stay for too long :) They came rather late, but that's understandable since it was Vyte's birthday and they decided to celebrate it by hitchhiking to Skagen and then to my place. We were playing boardgames the whole night, and I managed to fall in love with Monopoly Deal (what a game, seriously) and this Lithuanian game where you are supposed to place certain historical events on a timeline (and learned about the existence of the mighty Sniego ≈Ωmogus thanks to it). Cool, friendly, outgoing people that nobody should miss at their place!

She is a very cheerful and crazy (in good way) girl! She showed me around the city and we saw a lot more f weird things and beautiful places. I was so lucky to meet such a wonderful host since this is my first time to use Couchsurfing!!! We talked a lot and had very good time:D

Vytene has hosted me for a while in her nice apartment situated in the centre of the city.  She was a really nice person with an interesting life view. Vytene cooked some amazing food for me, I don't know the name but it tasted awesome. She showed me around a few secret places in Horsens. She also has a huge collection of board games, some of them are really addictive. Careful playing Monopoly Deal with her, she's a badass in it!

This was my first time couchsurfing and thanks to Vita it went amazing.  She is an easy-going, open-minded and friendly Lithuanian whom you want to hang out with. She showed me and my friend around the city, told a lot about the students life in Horsens and shared few precious tips about traveling.  We cooked together and played  a nice board game  (never ever try to beat  Vytenƒó :) Her flat was really cozy with awesome pics of her adventures all over the walls ^^
Dƒókoju Vytenƒó  and keep in touch :)

Vyte answered my last minute request very quickly, and she was also very nice to me and my friend. Thanks to her we saw the beach (the most beautiful place in Horsens), her university (from the top of the roof), played board games and tried a new shopping experience. Vyte is a very interesting and polite person, her flat is very neat and cozy. I finally had an opportunity to cook!!! Thank you for everything, we had a good time

Vytenƒó is a sweet girl, maybe at the first glance shy but she has adventurous Lithuanian soul which is great for Couchsurfing hosting and meeting people. 
Thanks to her she accepted me to stay at her couch and we had great time together. 
House was cozy and clean, we cooked some food together and had a nice conversations.  
Oh, yea, and the location is perfect, it's in the city center so everything is extremely close. 
I can recommend Vytenƒó as a host! :)
Kasper is a really friendly guy. Was a pleasure to host him.
Kasper is an easygoing cool no-nonsense easy to host guy.  We had great conversations, a beer and a lot of smiles and laughter during his short stay. Welcome back anytime Kasper.
Kasper and his friend, Laura are great people - we had fun going out together, they are nice and polite surfers.

Jurgita stayed less 12h before she and her friend has to hit the road again but it was enough time to get acquainted, have a nice chat and soup. they were nice and respectful, so definitely recommended guests! see you around the world :)

Jurgita is the most adorable person I've ever met. She is very open-minded, energetic and super friendly girl with positive attitude and incredible life experiences. Felt in love with such a personality from the very beginning:))
Jurgita stayed at my place in Hamburg for one night and it was really fun! She is very energetic and always up for everything I suggested! We explored the city and had my favourite food :)
Very intelligent girl. Lots of stories to tell. Just LOVED her!

Jurgita and Sergey stayed with us for a night and we were together during the weekend. They are so friendly, talkative, briefly great fellows. I hope we will meet up again and have an everlasting bond of friendship.

Jurgita is a super lovely girl! She is very active, funny and has a great sense of humor. :)  She and her friend stayed for 2 nights, and it was really nice to have them at my place. She is a really great person, and I hope to see her somewhere again - if you are given the opportunity to meet/ host Jurgita. Do it! :)

She is a very active and independent person. She shared me her interesting life stories which is kept updating every single day. We talk a lot and had great time! We would meet again somewhere on the earth:D

text: She help in all that she can help, this is more that I can expected. She share the food and she prefer to sleep in the coach to give me her bed. Is a girl to share good moments. We had a good time with her.

They were easy going with beeing on their own and left my flat spotlessly clean. I would host them definitely again.

I had a great introduction to Denmark by staying with Nicolas. He lives in a quiet town where streets are usually empty, and people who walk around might not be real people. He showed me a bit of his new town, we walked to the "mountain" where we almost saw panorama and we exchanged our traditional folk music. I had good time with him and his girlfriend and I can recommend him as a host or a guest to anyone. Thank you Nicolas and welcome to Serbia if happens to be on your way :)

text: I had a very nice stay at anne and luc's place. I mad a little bit of garden work while they prepared dinner. They are very nice people talking to and we chatted almost the entire stay. I can only refommened staying with these warm people.

We are grateful to have spent quality time in Saksild in the vast Danish countryside with a kind, warm and welcoming couple! 

Anne is a talented lady who can plant many things in the garden, make jams, freshly pressed apple juice, traditional Danish food. Luc has good sense of humor, knowledgeable about many subjects, and has a talent for making omelettes. There is a intelligent adorable cat in the house. 

Our bedrooms were clean, tidy and we slept very well. The house has many art works and indoor plants. We visited a lovely farm which 
had a fantastic bakery, delicatessen, coffee shop, flowers and farm animals. A modern farm with cows where you could put coins into a machine and get a carton of fresh Milk! Watched an inspiring film in a local cinema. 

We got an authentic Danish experience, learnt many interesting things about Danish culture thanks to Anne and Luc. They were superb hosts who are curious about other cultures, very considerate and happy individuals. Tak Tak!

I've had a really good night Luc and Anne, it's was really good for me to feel home again after being 6 months in Denmark. They made some nice food, we talked about lot of inspiring stuff! You are welcome at home dear Luc and Anne!

Incredible people! Very open and welcoming, with a lot to share. Made us a really nice home cooked meal our first night, with hens from their neighbors. Would very much like to stay again if i head that way!
10/10

Probably one of the souvenirs that i won't forget, Ann & Luc were the most adorable, amazing people i met, they very nice people, to be honest, i'm in lack of words to describe them properly, and the contact was immediat, and they made feel like i'm home with my family, we had long talks about everything, they helped me a lot during my jounrey in Aarhus and Ann showed me some parts of her region that i wouldn't be able to discover if i was there on my own.
This was my first couchsurfing experience, and i couldn't ask for more nice and open minded people like Ann & Luc, and now, i cannot wait to invite them to Algeria, so they can explore a country that weren't in their list, and show them my amazing country and family. <3

text: Luc and Anne are awesome hosts. They are generous, easygoing, and openminded, curious about life and other people, and interesting to talk with on a host of issues. They have loads of great recommendations for things to do and see in the surrounding area. I particularly enjoyed Luc's stories about living on the Faroe islands, and visiting the lovely cinema where Anna has volunteered for many years, as well as the farm where she grew up, where her sister now runs a bakery, butcher shop, restaurant, cafe and food store full of tasty local products. I'm truly glad I got the chance to meet this couple, and to stay in the wonderfully peaceful and bucolic home they have built together in Saksild. Their cat Mieu is one of the finest felines I've ever encountered. And Anne, you're right, as far as I'm concerned, the beach at Saksild is the finest in Denmark! :) Many thanks to you both. I hope to see you soon.

The last 2 days Simon und Robert have been our guests. It was a very positive and awe-inspiring experience to hear the stories of them both. On their way from Denmark to India by bike they stopped by in Greifswald too. They stayed for two nights. The first night they both slept on our couch. Unfortunatly that was not possible the second night. But as they did an unplaned stopover in my office anyway - to update and work on their tourdiary and blog >www.robertoglykkebybike.dk< - they simply stayed in my office for the night. They both are extremely likeable and down-to-earth,  openminded and eager for knowledge. Whenever they stop by and ask for a stay at yours, accommodate them and listen to their stories. Sure you will be impressed! Wish you all the best in the world and a successful journey full of events. I'm sure we will meet again. At least in Potsdam in a year at Roberts new caravan! *bigsmile*
response: {'id': '1562667', 'text': "I and my travel companion Surfed two nights at Gritt and Ronnie's place, or more precisely, places. They were very helpfull from the start. First of all they answered very fast, and they offered that we could put our bicycles in their basement, they were curious to know about our tour to India, and our bikes, as They do alot of sports themselves. Their couch gave us a really great and deep rest. Generally speaking, it was so easy to feel at home at their place. They are open, humorous and full of good tips and tricks.
